                    <span class="opener__topics  opener__topics--vertical-rule -is-over-bg opener__topics--light">
            <a class="opener__topics-link  -is-over-bg opener__topics-link--light" href="https://www.propublica.org/topics/environment">Environment</a>
        </span>
    
    <h1 class="opener__hed  opener__hed--vertical-rule -is-over-bg opener__hed--light opener__hed--small" >        How 3M Executives Convinced a Scientist the Forever Chemicals She Found in Human Blood Were Safe
    </h1>

        <h2 class="opener__dek  -is-over-bg opener__dek--light" >        Decades ago, Kris Hansen showed 3M that its PFAS chemicals were in people’s bodies. Her bosses halted her work. As the EPA now forces the removal of the chemicals from drinking water, she wrestles with the secrets that 3M kept from her and the world.
    </h2>
    
            <div class="article-meta-1  -is-over-bg article-meta-1--light">
            <span class="article-meta-1__byline">
                by <a class="name" href="https://www.propublica.org/people/sharon-lerner">Sharon Lerner</a>, photography by <span class="name">Haruka Sakaguchi</span>, special to <a href="https://www.propublica.org">ProPublica</a>            </span>
            <time class="article-meta-1__pubdate">
                <time class="timestamp" datetime="2024-05-20EDT06:00">May 20, 6 a.m. EDT</time>
            </time>
        </div>
    
    </div> <!-- Close .opener__topic-title-dek-wrapper -->

    
</div>
        
